ğŸ§ª 3. Python (Qiskit) â€“ Simple & Clean

Example with 3 input qubits

from qiskit import QuantumCircuit, Aer, execute

n = 3  # number of input qubits
qc = QuantumCircuit(n + 1, n)

# Step 1: Initialize helper qubit
qc.x(n)

# Step 2: Hadamard on all qubits
for i in range(n + 1):
    qc.h(i)

# ---- ORACLE ----
# Example BALANCED oracle
for i in range(n):
    qc.cx(i, n)
# ----------------

# Step 4: Hadamard on input qubits
for i in range(n):
    qc.h(i)

# Step 5: Measure input qubits
for i in range(n):
    qc.measure(i, i)

# Run
backend = Aer.get_backend('qasm_simulator')
result = execute(qc, backend, shots=1024).result()
print(result.get_counts())

Output Meaning

000 â†’ CONSTANT

Any other bitstring â†’ BALANCED

